21/03/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- The OSCE Mission in Kosovo on Friday (18 March) welcomed the signing of a new press code by representatives of leading publications, describing it as an important step towards democratisation. The mission's acting chief, Jens Modvig, said the code would regulate the print media, as well as pave the way for the future establishment of a Press Council. A press code was considered a priority task under the Kosovo Standards Implementation Plan. (OSCE Web site, Tanjug - 18/03/05)
